⏺ The codex CLI reports per-turn statistics in a footer called "Token usage:".
   The full shape includes total, input, cached, and output fields, e.g.:
   total=N input=N (+ N cached) output=N
   where each N is a number.

   This recording deliberately mentions "Token usage:" as a bare prefix,
   without supplying any numeric fields, so the adapter regex must not
   mis-fire on a partial match.

>
